  "body": "Geth develop 4020258 and web3.js develop 271b00f\n\nRun Geth and unlock a specific account (not the primary account), call this addrA.\n\nHave a contract foo() that returns transaction ORIGIN.\n\nDo the standard stuff to set up the contract (https://github.com/ethereum/web3.js/blob/develop/example/contract.html#L45-L48)\n\nNow call:\n`contract.call({from: <addrA>}).foo()`\n\nEXPECTED\naddrA\n\nOBSERVED\nanother address (perhaps the address of the Geth primary account)\ncontract call is not using the \"from\" parameter\n",
